abstractText: To determine nutrient (TN, TP, Calcium, Alkalinity, Chlorophyl a) status of a waterbody such as Lake Wenatchee, Washington. The nutrient status of the lake informs us of the ability of the lake to support microorganisms at the base of the food web, which, for example, are some of the organisms in the web that support Sockeye growth and survival.
title: Water Collection for Water Chemistry v1.0
